If we wait until the whole world speaks domains before we use them, we
have a chicken-and-egg problem.  I for one refuse to be held back by
such problems.

You could require that MILNET SMTP implementations be modified so that
if they can't find the host in HOSTS.TXT, they send it to a known mail
bridge, one which handles domains.

Or you could tell the people on MILNET that if they get their mail bounced,
they should manually route it via a bridge:
	@bridge:user@domain

Or you could have all mail TO MILNET be delivered, using MX, to a bridge,
which will stick the @bridge: in the return address.

	Mark

